HEADWORD: Testification
<hw>Tes`ti*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>testificatio</ets>: cf. OF. <ets>testification</ets>. See
<er>Testify</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of testifying, or giving testimony
or evidence; <as>as, a direct <ex>testification</ex> of our homage to
God</as>.</def> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

